		<hr size="1">Bards don't need to med until they start using the charm songs if I am not mistaken as they are the only ones that take mana.  I used to play rallos, and couldn't stand it, so I went to a blue server.</P><P>But to answer your question, speed is your greatest asset, NOTHING, and I mean NOTHING can outrun a bard on selo's, save a higher level bard.  If you are playing on rallos where people can loot 1 item, get your newbie no drop armor to start off with so you don't have to worry about bagging before you get killed.</P><P>As to PvPing, again, speed is your greatest asset.  The best PVPers I saw would hit and run before you could hit them back, and since nothing can outrun you, just run in, hit them with your sword/club/dagger, then run off, twisting songs like selo's to keep yourself moving faster then they are, chord's of discord if no mobs are about you can aggro, and Brusco's, just keep doing this until your target is dead, and if they zone out, watch your back.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
